rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0007
rows.name: Rex not pro salvager for nothing.

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0009
rows.name:
I think your experiences salvaging
really came in useful!

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0010
rows.name:
Not that I don't appreciate the
compliments, but we should hurry
and rescue Nia.

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0011
rows.name: Boss not very good at games?

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0012
rows.name:
I...I can't help it, can I?!
It was my first time playing!

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0014
rows.name: A-anyway, let's focus on Nia for now!

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0001
rows.name:
So, how are we going to get
onto that Divine Beast battleship
where Nia's being held...?

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0002
rows.name:
From here, is easiest to go up to top of
stairs, cross bridge, then pass under
gate, then you're at Garagorm's Arch!

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0003
rows.name: Will the Superbian guards not spot us?

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0004
rows.name:
Area around Superbian base heavily
guarded, but up to Garagorm's Arch
should be no problem!

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0005
rows.name: All right. Let's head there for now!

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0015
rows.name: Hana will do best to help.

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0016
rows.name:
As luck would have it, the Cloud Sea
looks to be ebbing just now. We had
best aim for the root Homura mentioned.

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0017
rows.name:
The root was stretchy-stretching
just past Garagorm's Arch!
